To pull data using SQL (or HQL, which is the Hibernate Query Language for querying databases in Hibernate) with two conditions through a repository, you need to create a query method in your repository interface. Assuming you are using Spring Data JPA, here&#39;s an example:

Let&#39;s say you have an entity named Your Entity and a repository interface named Your Entity Repository. Here&#39;s how you can create a method to retrieve data based on twoimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;
import org.springframework.data.repository.query.Param;
import java.util.List;

public interface Your Entity Repository extends Jpa Repository&lt;YourEntity, Long&gt; {

    @Query(&quot;SELECT e FROM Your Entity e WHERE e.condition1 = :condition1 AND e.condition2 = :condition2&quot;)
    List&lt;YourEntity&gt; find By Conditions(@Param(&quot;condition1&quot;) TypeOfCondition1 condition1, @Param(&quot;condition2&quot;) TypeOfCondition2 condition2);

    // You can also use method naming conventions without @Query annotation
    List&lt;Your Entity&gt; findByCondition1AndCondition2(TypeOfCondition1 condition1, TypeOfCondition2 condition2);
}
 in the above example:

YourEntity is the name of your entity class.
condition1 and condition2 are placeholders for the actual conditions you want to use in your query. Replace them with the actual field names and types in your entity.
TypeOfCondition1 and TypeOfCondition2 are the types of your conditions. Replace them with the actual types of your conditions.
findByConditions is the custom query method name, and it uses the @Query annotation to define the HQL query.
You can also use Spring Data JPA&#39;s method naming conventions, as shown in the second example, where you define the method using the field names in the entity and concatenate them with &quot;And&quot;. This will automatically generate the query based on the method name.

Remember to replace the placeholder names with the actual names and types from your entity. This is just a general example to illustrate the concept. please do vote my answer if it helped you or if you feel the answer was correct

